full_text: A new account can be created for a person or a company. To create a new account, the user must have the permission to do so. For example, log in as a producer, Archie Armstrong. In this demo, we will cover the basics of creating a new account for a person. Click the Account tab at the top. Select New Account. First, it goes through the name clearance process to check if there is already an existing account. Enter the first name. Enter the last name. Click Search. It returns zero results. Click Create New Account. You can either create a new one by selecting Person, or create the account based on a matching contact by searching the address of the account. Click the address box. Let's select Person from the drop-down. Enter the address information. After you enter City, State, or Zip Code, it tries to auto-fill the rest. Start typing in the City field. Select from the list of suggested cities. The State and Zip Code are auto-filled. Select an address type. Next, you must select a producer code, which is a unique identifier that Policy Center uses to track which agents set up and service the account. In this example, the producer code should be Armstrong Premier from Armstrong & Company. Click the search icon to find the organization quickly. To search for Armstrong, type the first couple of letters of the organization name. Click Search. Select Armstrong and Company. Select the producer code, Armstrong Premier. Click Update. The account is created, and an account number is assigned. The account summary dashboard provides several information panels with details about the account holder, a general overview of the account and policies. Accounts can be edited. The account holder information can be updated, if needed. Let's just cancel out of it. The account has a status of Pending. If there are no active policies, you can withdraw the account by clicking Actions. Select Withdraw Account. The status changes to Withdraw. The status changes to Withdraw. You can reopen it by clicking Actions. Select Reopen Account. The status changes back to Pending.
